lementor-size-sm\" type=\"submit\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"elementor-button-content-wrapper\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"elementor-button-text\">Send<\/span>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/span>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/button>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/form>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-4f0aa95 elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"4f0aa95\" data-element_type=\"section\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-18aaa6c\" data-id=\"18aaa6c\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-38202cd elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"38202cd\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Body Structure of Cigarette Beetles<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-6498f48 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"6498f48\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Cigarette beetles are small insects that belong to the family of Anobiidae. They have an oval-shaped body with a reddish-brown color and measure about 2-3mm in length. Cigarette beetles possess distinctive antennae with serrated edges, which help them locate food sources quickly. Their elytra, or hardened forewings, are covered in tiny hairs that give them a velvety appearance.<\/p>\n<p>Underneath their exoskeleton, cigarette beetles have three pairs of legs and two pairs of wings. The hindwings are membranous and fold neatly beneath the elytra when not in use. Cigarette beetles also have large compound eyes that detect light and movement around them.<\/p>\n<p>The body structure of cigarette beetles plays a crucial role in their survival as they can easily penetrate packaging materials such as cardboard boxes or plastic bags to access food sources.<\/p>\n<p>The protection of your home and belongings from the likes of cigarette beetles,&nbsp;<a href=\"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/furniture-beetles\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><u><b>furniture beetles<\/b><\/u><\/a>,&nbsp;<u><b><a href=\"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/drugstore-beetles\/\">drugstore beetles<\/a><\/b><\/u>, and&nbsp;<a href=\"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/grain-beetles\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><u><b>grain beetles<\/b><\/u><\/a>&nbsp;with our expert-recommended pest control methods<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-77ba4a5 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"77ba4a5\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Habitat: Where do cigarette beetles live?<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-043d382 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"043d382\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Cigarette beetles, also known as tobacco beetles, are tiny insects belonging to the Anobiidae family. These pests are notorious for infesting dried plant products and stored food items. Cigarette beetles are commonly found in homes, warehouses, grocery stores, and other places where such products are available. The ideal habitat for cigarette beetles is warm and humid environments. They can be found worldwide due to their ability to adapt well to different environments.<\/p><p>Cigarette beetles can live anywhere from two months up to a year, depending on environmental conditions. They often hide in cracks and crevices or inside packaged goods like cigars, tobacco leaves, rice grains, flour bags or pet food containers. To avoid an infestation of cigarette beetles in your home or workplace, it&#8217;s important to keep stored foods properly sealed at all times.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-e259f12 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"e259f12\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Diet: What do cigarette beetles eat?<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-ec1a701 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"ec1a701\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Cigarette beetles are a type of pest that can cause significant damage to stored food products. These beetles feed on various organic materials, including grains, cereals, spices, and tobacco. Cigarette beetles are named for their affinity for feeding on dried tobacco leaves.<\/p><p>Despite their name, cigarette beetles don&#8217;t just eat tobacco &#8211; they will also consume many other types of foods commonly found in homes and businesses. The most frequently targeted items include flour, pasta, pet food, and even natural fibers like wool or silk. Additionally, cigarette beetle infestations often begin with an initial introduction via contaminated food products brought into the home from outside sources.<\/p><p>To prevent these pests from infiltrating your pantry or storage areas, it&#8217;s important to store all dry goods in sealed containers and scrutinize any new purchases before bringing them inside. If you suspect a cigarette beetle infestation in your home or business, contact a pest control professional to discuss treatment options and develop a plan to protect your property from further damage.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-0812a61 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"0812a61\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Behavior: How do cigarette beetles behave?<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-1f10e1b elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"1f10e1b\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Cigarette beetles are small, reddish-brown insects that belong to the family Anobiidae. They are named so because they have a notorious habit of infesting tobacco products like cigarettes, cigars, and pipe tobacco. These beetles feed on other dried plant materials such as spices, cereals, and dried fruits. Adult cigarette beetles are about 2-3 mm long and have an oval-shaped body.<\/p><p>The behavior of cigarette beetles is quite similar to other types of stored product pests. The female beetle lays eggs on suitable food sources, hatching into larvae that feed on the material around them. This can cause significant damage and contamination to stored products over time. Cigarette beetles prefer warm temperatures (above 70\u00b0F) and high humidity levels (above 75%). They are active fliers and can easily spread from one location to another if not controlled promptly.<\/p><p>In addition to being a nuisance for homeowners, cigarette beetles can pose serious health hazards by contaminating food items with feces or dead bodies. It is important to take preventive measures such as storing dry goods in airtight containers, cleaning pantry areas regularly, and working with a pest control professional if an infestation is suspected or detected.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-a97775b elementor-section-full_width elementor-section-stretched elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"a97775b\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;stretch_section&quot;:&quot;section-stretched&quot;,&quot;background_background&quot;:&quot;classic&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-33 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-eb56515\" data-id=\"eb56515\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-33 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-f8e7d97\" data-id=\"f8e7d97\" data-element_type=\"column\" data-settings=\"{&quot;background_background&quot;:&quot;classic&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-8e90733 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"8e90733\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Residential Pest Control Service<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<